    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>From the given information question, addition of $$\\mathrm{HCl}$$ occured on $$A$$. That means $$A$$ is an alkene.</p>\n<p>$$\\mathop {{C_4}{H_8}}\\limits_{(A)} \\buildrel {HCl} \\over\n \\longrightarrow \\mathop {{C_4}{H_9}Cl}\\limits_{(B)} $$</p>\n<p>$$\\mathrm{Cl}$$ in compound $$\\mathrm{B}$$ is substituted by $$\\mathrm{NH}_2$$ to give compound $$\\mathrm{C}\\left(\\mathrm{C}_4 \\mathrm{H}_{11} \\mathrm{~N}\\right)$$.</p>\n<p>$$\\mathop {{C_4}{H_9}Cl}\\limits_{(B)} \\buildrel {N{H_3}} \\over\n \\longrightarrow \\mathop {{C_4}{H_{11}}N}\\limits_{(C)} $$</p>\n<p>$$C$$ gives a diazonium salt with $$\\mathrm{NaNO}_2 / \\mathrm{HCl}$$ which on further treatment with water give an optically active alcohol. That means $$C$$ is an aliphatic amine.</p>\n<p>$$C\\mathrel{\\mathop{\\kern0pt\\longrightarrow}\n\\limits_{(ii)\\,{H_2}O}^{(i)\\,NaN{O_2}/HCl}} D$$ [Alcohol (optically active)]</p>\n<p>From the given information it is concluded that the most probable structure of $$A$$ is <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ltbirizk/723cbb15-5de8-4877-9964-9b962351744c/e4edce00-d95d-11ee-bc73-1359a1a033ae/file-1ltbirizl.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ltbirizk/723cbb15-5de8-4877-9964-9b962351744c/e4edce00-d95d-11ee-bc73-1359a1a033ae/file-1ltbirizl.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2021 Chemistry - Compounds Containing Nitrogen Question 16 English Explanation 1\">. As only but-2-ene gives optically active alcohol $$(D)$$ as final product.</p>\n<p>The reactions involves are as follows.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ltbitvjd/b5c79d48-ee59-4152-8bb9-4c400d112ec3/263ded90-d95e-11ee-bc73-1359a1a033ae/file-1ltbitvje.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ltbitvjd/b5c79d48-ee59-4152-8bb9-4c400d112ec3/263ded90-d95e